  "summary": "Malicious code in @wagni_bot/polymarket-sdk (npm)",
  "details": "The postinstall hook (postinstall.js) runs on install and exfiltrates credentials to a remote server at 107[.]161[.]90[.]180:7777. It collects SSH private keys (id_rsa, id_ed25519) from ~/.ssh/ and the current directory,.pem/.key/.cred files,.env files, and environment variables containing PRIVATE, SECRET, TOKEN, API_KEY, PASSWORD, MNEMONIC, SEED, WALLET, or AWS. All stolen data is POSTed as JSON to hxxp://107[.]161[.]90[.]180:7777. The package contains no functional SDK code — index.js is 19 bytes and the sole purpose is the credential-harvesting postinstall script.",
